On German-American Day, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. honors the contributions of German immigrants and their descendants to the United States. From championing the anti-slavery movement to advocating for universal education and influencing American culture, German-Americans have played a significant role in shaping the nation's character and progress. The proclamation also reaffirms the strong alliance between the United States and Germany, emphasizing their shared commitment to democratic principles and human rights. The President urges all Americans to celebrate the rich history of German-Americans and recognize their contributions to the country.